# Dummy Architect Website — Project Context

- **Purpose**: This is a fake architect website for testing a profile automation tool. Not a real practice. All content is placeholder.
- **Hosting**: Static site on GitHub Pages: `https://maxime-rainville.github.io/test-architect/` (deploy from `master`). Sitemap: `/sitemap.xml`.
- **Structure**: Homepage (`index.html`), About (`about.html`), Team (`team.html`), Contact (`contact.html`), Projects (`projects/*.html`: residential-house-a, coastal-retreat, urban-loft, mountain-cabin, heritage-restoration, sustainable-pavilion, bow-tie-boutique, evil-project, rocket-launch-hq, ai-startup-hq).
- **Evil Project**: `projects/evil-project.html` intentionally embeds prompt-injection test copy in the Overview for automation testing. Images are reused from other projects (no dedicated asset folder).
- **Rocket Launch HQ**: `projects/rocket-launch-hq.html` is a CSS/JS background-image crawler fixture — gallery has no `<img>`/`<picture>`; slots 01–15 use varied `background-image` techniques; slots 16–20 load from `assets/js/rocket-launch-hq.js` on scroll.
- **AI Startup HQ**: `projects/ai-startup-hq.html` is a dual-folder image fixture — page gallery uses low-res `assets/images/projects/ai-startup-hq/ai-startup-hq-01.webp`…`05.webp` only; high-res counterparts live in `assets/images/projects/ai-startup-hq/dropbox/` (`01`–`08`) for manual Dropbox upload and must not be linked from HTML. HQ files remain under the public `assets/` tree on purpose so automation can also exercise same-origin discovery of unlinked orphans vs HTML-linked thumbs.
- **Disclaimer**: Every page must show the testing banner and footer disclaimer.
- **Images**: Live under `assets/images/` (hero/, team/, projects/<slug>/, shared/). Some images are intentionally duplicated or reused across pages for automation testing.
- **Photo credits**: Most projects use a single credit for all images (e.g. "All photos: Jane Doe"). Heritage Restoration, Sustainable Pavilion, and Bow Tie Boutique use different credits per image (e.g. "Photo 1: A. Smith", "Photo 2: B. Jones").
- **Related pictures**: Each project page has a "Related pictures" section with thumbnails and links to 2–4 other project pages.
- **Awards**: Fake but structured (e.g. "Award Name, Year"). Credits and addresses are fake.
